Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a jelly roll pan with foil; spray with nonstick cooking spray. Combine cornflakes, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper in a shallow dish. Lightly beat egg in another shallow dish. Wash hands. Rinse ice glaze off chicken. Pat dry. Dip chicken in egg, then in cornflakes mixture. Place on pan. Wash hands Drizzle chicken with butter. Bake 20 minutes or until done (internal temp 170 degrees F).